            "description": "Co-founding a social movement to collect coins and loose changes; resulting in \"a chance\" to send Indonesian kids back to school. \n\nThe movement has been adopted in 10 cities all across Indonesia, and has received an award from Nokia Indonesia as The Best Online Activism 2009, an award from Merck for their #KlikHati program in 2010, became one of the finalists in Liputan 6 Award for Education category in 2010 and Gatra magazine's icon for social sector in 2010, as well as being featured in Forbes Indonesia magazine. \n\nCoin A Chance! had also worked hand-in-hand in several collaborative campaigns with respected companies like Coca-Cola Indonesia, Nivea Men, BodyShop, Citibank, XL Axiata, Mandala Tiger Air, and many more, and had made its way to one of Indonesia's most respected and prestigious talk show, KickAndy, in Metro TV.\n\nYou can also read one of our stories in The Jakarta Globe here: http://www.thejakartaglobe.com/count-me-in/using-loose-change-to-help-keep-indonesian-kids-in-school-2/",
